The paper proposes a framework for feature extraction from multiple data modalities, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision. The paper focuses on finding representations of individual modalities that are maximally correlated, which is a key problem in the field of multimodal learning. The paper also discusses the use of semi-supervised learning to enhance the discriminative power of the feature representations. Based on these factors, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also discusses the use of discriminative models, which suggests a possible fit with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
